notes.title: Project Ideas
notes.textContent: Build a personal knowledge base app that uses AI to organize notes automatically. Features: voice input, smart tagging, cross-reference suggestions, and weekly digests.

notes.title: Books to Read
notes.textContent:
1. Atomic Habits by James Clear
2. The Pragmatic Programmer
3. Designing Data-Intensive Applications
4. Deep Work by Cal Newport
5. The Mom Test

notes.title: Coffee Shop Recommendations
notes.textContent:
Blue Bottle Coffee on 5th Ave - amazing pour over, great for working remotely. Try their New Orleans iced coffee!

Philz Coffee downtown - best mint mojito coffee. Gets crowded after 10am.

Local roasters on Main St - cozy atmosphere, excellent pastries.

notes.title: Learning Resources
notes.textContent:
Great tutorials and courses I found:

- MIT OpenCourseWare: Algorithms and Data Structures
-System Design Primer on GitHub
- Fireship.io YouTube channel for quick tech overviews
- PostgreSQL documentation - surprisingly well written

notes.title: Gift Ideas
notes.textContent:
Birthday gifts for family:
- Mom: noise-canceling headphones (Sony or Bose)
- Dad: book on woodworking or new tools
- Sister: art supplies or museum membership
- Brother: mechanical keyboard (he's been eyeing the Keychron Q1)
